The documents provide definitions and descriptions of what an "Offbeat" film is, indicating that it is indeed a type of film. The term "offbeat" refers to films that are different from the ordinary, usual, or expected (document 121), and the Offbeat project started as a tribute to British directors who made good, solid films with an enduring oddness or uniqueness to them (documents 28 and 43).
